article.headline: Eagles nearly double up on Tigers in first half
article.linkText: Going quietly: Savannah State stays winless
article.story: SAVANNAH, Ga. (AP) -- Elton Nesbitt scored 19 points to lead five Georgia Southern players in double figures Monday night in a 92-64 victory over Savannah State, the only team in NCAA Division I to remain winless. The Eagles (13-8) led from the beginning, starting with a 3-pointer by Terry Williams 50 seconds into the game, and almost doubled the scoring by Savannah State (0-24) with a 46-24 halftime lead. Georgia Southern led much of the second half by about 30 points, bulging to 34 points at 7:10 to play, and had a 92-62 advantage when the Tigers' Alvin Edwards hit a layup with three seconds left for the final margin. Jean Francois scored 16 points, Williams and Donte Gennie had 12 apiece, and Louis Graham had 11 points and 13 rebounds for the Eagles. Savannah State shot just 37.9 percent (22-58) for the game and was outrebounded 51-39. Sherard Reddick led the Tigers with 21 points and eight rebounds.
